description.narrative: Development of Social and Behaviour Change Communication (SBCC) strategy plan with Ministry of Health (MoH) is one of the successful example strategies to reduce and halt overweight and obesity among children. This strategy plan was informed by formative research that established key behaviour issues to facilitate interventions to promote positive nutrition outcomes in the short and longer terms. UNICEF is scaling up efforts to prevent child malnutrition in response to the impact of COVID19, where nutrition priorities should be integrated into the national social protection plan. Policy brief on COVID19 and Nutrition will be developed for advocating high-level decision-makers. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:09/09/2019
